# Marketplace Builder Hackathon 2025

This repository is for the **Marketplace Builder Hackathon 2025**. It includes a project structure, a self-validation checklist, and resources to help participants succeed in the hackathon.

---

## Project Overview

The Marketplace Builder Hackathon is an exciting opportunity to develop a functional and responsive marketplace application. This repository provides a starting point for participants, with boilerplate code and guidelines to streamline the development process.

### Features:
- Responsive UI design using Next.js
- Product listing and filtering functionalities
- User authentication and profile management
- Backend integration for dynamic content

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (version 14 or above)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) or [yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/)
- A GitHub account

### Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone <repository-url>
   cd marketplace-builder-hackathon-2025
   ```

2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   npm install
   ```

3. Run the development server:
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```
   The application will be available at `http://localhost:3000`.

